news.title: Japan's land prices fall due to covid-19
news.para: Overall property prices in the world's third-largest economy fell 0.4% in the year to July after last year's 0.6% decline, which was the first fall in three years, a land ministry survey showed on Tuesday.

news.title: Madras HC refuses to vacate stay against stone quarries in Tamil Nadu
news.para: Originally, taking into account the pollution caused by stone crushing units, the Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board had issued a set of guidelines in 2004, stipulating no such quarries can be allowed within 500 meters from residential areas, national and state highways and places of worship.

news.title: Puranik Builders files draft papers with Sebi again to raise funds via IPO
news.para: ​The IPO comprises fresh issue of shares worth Rs 510 crore and an offer for sale up to 945,000 equity shares by the company's promoters group, according to the draft papers filed with Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) on Monday.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing's Rs 200 crore NCDs public issue oversubscribed four times
news.para: Base Issue was oversubscribed by 4.04 times with a total collection of Rs 807.83 crore while the retail category oversubscribed by 2.44 times with a total collection of Rs 146.22 crore.

news.title: Inflation forces homebuilders in USA to take it slow, raise prices
news.para: Rising costs and shortages of building materials and labor are rippling across the homebuilding industry, which accounted for nearly 12% of all U.S. home sales in July.

news.title: Sunrays Infrastructure to develop 1.4 lakh sq ft commercial space in Faridabad
news.para: The company has tied up with IQI India (Global Real Estate Advisory Firm) for feasible and retail operations dynamic based occupancy bringing business goal achievements.

news.title: ​How far will Xi Jinping go to restrain China's real estate sector?
news.para: Even though most people don’t expect Evergrande to collapse all of a sudden, the silence and a lack of major actions from policy makers is making everyone panic, said an economist.

news.title: US stocks fall on fears of contagion from China real estate
news.para: Worries about debt-engorged Chinese property developers - and the damage they could do to investors worldwide if they default - are rippling across markets.

news.title: Punjab cabinet deliberates on making sand available at affordable rates
news.para: Earlier in the day, Channi, Randhawa and Soni were administered the oath by the governor. Channi is the first Dalit chief minister of Punjab. The cabinet discussed various "pro-poor" initiatives to be implemented in a time-bound manner.

news.title: SC seeks details of structures still standing on forest land in Khori village
news.para: The civic body counsel informed the bench also comprising Justice Dinesh Maheshwari that up to September 15, a total of 2,391 applications for rehabilitation have been received so far, out of which 892 applicants were found to be prima facie eligible.

news.title: Punjab cabinet directs housing department to construct 32,000 EWS homes
news.para: The Cabinet directed the Housing and Urban Development Department to start the construction of houses for 32,000 economically weaker section (EWS) on priority.

news.title: HDFC offers home loan at 6.7%
news.para: HDFC said, "Customers can avail HDFC Home Loan starting at 6.70 per cent per annum effective September 20, 2021. This offer will be applicable to all new loan applications irrespective of the loan amount or employment category.

news.title: Is Evergrande another Lehman? China probably won't let the builder go that way
news.para: Should a Lehman-style crisis spiral out from Evergrande, the impact would be dramatic. Just how dramatic, though? A look at past steel crises gives some clues.

news.title: Evergrande troubles punish China property as contagion concern spreads
news.para: A major test comes this week, with Evergrande due to pay $83.5 million in interest relating to its March 2022 bond on Thursday. It has another $47.5 million payment due on Sept. 29 for March 2024 notes.

news.title: Karnataka assembly passes bill slashing stamp duty by 2% on flats priced below Rs 45 lakh
news.para: Revenue Minister R Ashoka said lakhs of flats in Bengaluru and in other cities have remained unsold due to the distress caused by the Covid-19 pandemic. The stamp duty reduction, he said, will help both the real estate sector which is struggling with a pile of inventory as well as low-income group families.
